03:36.363 --> 03:38.396
[SIRENS WAILING]

03:40.901 --> 03:42.968
We need to get off the road.

03:42.970 --> 03:44.236
[TIRES SCREECHING]

03:50.325 --> 03:52.077
Everybody out, quickly.

03:56.884 --> 03:58.917
We need to get us somewhere safer.

03:58.919 --> 04:00.752
I'm afraid this is the end of the line.

04:00.754 --> 04:02.220
We have to split up.

04:02.222 --> 04:05.056
What? But where do we go?

04:05.058 --> 04:06.524
As far as you can from the city.

04:06.526 --> 04:08.260
Stay off the main roads.

04:08.262 --> 04:10.437
Avoid traffic cameras, and...

04:10.440 --> 04:12.637
- don't trust humans.
- LAUREN: Are you crazy?

04:12.640 --> 04:13.715
They can't.

04:13.718 --> 04:16.125
We can't stay on the
road in this car any longer.

04:16.128 --> 04:18.837
Look, we have to scatter or
we're all gonna get caught.

04:18.839 --> 04:21.106
Okay? Run! Go!

04:21.108 --> 04:23.241
Lauren!

04:23.243 --> 04:25.076
[GRUNTS]

04:25.078 --> 04:26.845
[INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

04:28.615 --> 04:31.383
We'll take them! You go that way!

04:37.524 --> 04:39.624
This is all your fault.

04:39.626 --> 04:41.393
This is your fault.

04:42.763 --> 04:45.297
- You left her down there.
- Tried. I tried to bring...

04:45.300 --> 04:47.933
She shouldn't have been down
there in the first place!

04:47.935 --> 04:50.602
She chose to join us. I gave her a place

04:50.604 --> 04:52.237
where she belonged. Blink was...

04:52.239 --> 04:54.095
Stop calling her Blink!

04:54.098 --> 04:55.774
It's the name she chose!

04:57.477 --> 04:59.244
Now, I made mistakes,

04:59.246 --> 05:01.379
but I didn't lure her
down into the tunnels.

05:03.116 --> 05:05.250
You drove her to us.

05:05.252 --> 05:06.584
[SIRENS WAILING IN DISTANCE]

05:08.722 --> 05:10.322
Oh, you gonna hit me?

05:10.324 --> 05:12.757
Hit me.

05:12.759 --> 05:14.259
It's not gonna change anything.

05:22.970 --> 05:25.737
[GRUNTING]

05:25.739 --> 05:28.473
- [GLASS BREAKING]
- [GROANS]

05:28.475 --> 05:31.643
[WHIRRING, PULSATING WHOOSHING]

05:31.645 --> 05:34.145
Come on!

05:35.282 --> 05:37.315
Do it!

05:40.620 --> 05:41.987
[WHOOSHING STOPS]

05:45.792 --> 05:47.792
I'm sorry.

05:55.936 --> 05:57.168
[YELLS]

06:00.807 --> 06:03.708
The moment we've been waiting
for has finally arrived.

06:04.778 --> 06:07.178
Our actions in the next 24 hours

06:07.180 --> 06:10.348
will determine the
course of mutant history.

06:12.456 --> 06:15.687
Our uprising has been every
bit as successful as we'd hoped.

06:15.689 --> 06:20.125
And now it is perfectly clear
to mutants and humans alike

06:20.127 --> 06:21.693
that there is only one solution.

06:23.230 --> 06:25.230
Two nations, divided.

06:25.232 --> 06:27.699
Ours and theirs.

06:27.701 --> 06:29.701
We have worked hard.

06:29.703 --> 06:33.571
And one last push will
take us to our goal.

06:33.573 --> 06:37.875
We must destroy the institutions
of a nation that hates us.

06:37.878 --> 06:39.077
POLARIS: Hang on.

06:39.079 --> 06:41.479
We're just gonna destroy
government buildings?

06:41.481 --> 06:42.981
Have you seen the security out there?

06:42.983 --> 06:45.817
Don't worry. We have our ways.

06:45.819 --> 06:47.352
REEVA: Tonight,

06:47.354 --> 06:49.254
you'll be receiving your assignments.

06:49.256 --> 06:52.657
Until then, prepare yourselves.

06:57.364 --> 06:59.364
This is crazy.

06:59.366 --> 07:01.199
It's actually happening.

07:01.201 --> 07:03.435
- Hard to believe.
- Yeah.

07:13.046 --> 07:14.879
Stay back here with the others.

07:14.881 --> 07:16.337
Stay away from the windows.

07:16.340 --> 07:18.702
This place is safe, but
we can't take any chances.

07:18.705 --> 07:19.751
- [PHONE VIBRATING]
- ECLIPSE: Let's get them settled

07:19.753 --> 07:21.833
back there and head back
out. I'm worried about John.

07:23.457 --> 07:26.691
Reed? It's Lorna.

07:26.693 --> 07:28.560
Hey, I'm here with Reed. Are you okay?

07:28.562 --> 07:31.379
[QUIETLY]: Yeah, for
now. I can't talk long.

07:31.382 --> 07:33.487
Oh, I was so worried you got caught.

07:33.490 --> 07:34.818
Yeah, I almost was.

07:34.821 --> 07:37.102
The Frosts found out that
somebody was in the computers.

07:37.104 --> 07:38.570
They think it was Sage.

07:38.572 --> 07:40.138
Reeva killed her.

07:40.140 --> 07:42.085
What?

07:42.088 --> 07:43.908
Well, things are
spiraling out of control.

07:43.910 --> 07:45.743
The Purifiers just hit
the Morlock tunnels.

07:45.745 --> 07:47.579
It was a massacre.

07:47.581 --> 07:49.080
You've got to get out of there.

07:49.082 --> 07:51.282
I know, but Reeva's plan
is happening tomorrow.

07:51.284 --> 07:53.751
I'm gonna try to find out
what I can before I go.

07:53.753 --> 07:55.954
All right, just-just
come. We'll be ready.

07:55.956 --> 07:57.956
Lorna, what about Andy?

07:58.992 --> 08:01.059
I-I'm not sure.

08:01.061 --> 08:02.260
This is our last chance.

08:02.262 --> 08:04.062
- If he stays with her, then...
- I know,

08:04.064 --> 08:06.431
but he believes in what Reeva's doing.

08:06.433 --> 08:08.833
And if I can't convince him, then...

08:08.835 --> 08:11.095
then it's over...

08:11.098 --> 08:12.971
for all of us.

08:14.107 --> 08:17.075
You have to try. Lorna,

08:17.077 --> 08:19.110
tell him the truth.

08:19.112 --> 08:21.346
Please, Lorna...

08:22.415 --> 08:24.415
...bring my son home.

08:28.677 --> 08:31.344
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

08:34.855 --> 08:36.921
Most of the force is out
chasing down the muties

08:36.923 --> 08:38.923
who escaped from the tunnels.

08:38.924 --> 08:41.159
I showed 'em my badge,
told 'em what we knew,

08:41.160 --> 08:44.352
said we wanted to help
out. I figure we, uh,

08:44.355 --> 08:46.922
search the streets around
here for stragglers.

08:48.101 --> 08:49.434
Yeah, I don't, uh...

08:49.436 --> 08:51.035
I don't know about that.

08:53.240 --> 08:54.506
What do you mean?

08:55.251 --> 08:57.075
Those sons of bitches
killed three good men.

08:57.077 --> 08:58.409
We got to finish what we started.

08:58.411 --> 09:00.879
Yeah, I just...

09:03.283 --> 09:05.283
Guys, will you give us a minute?

09:07.621 --> 09:08.786
Hey, buddy.

09:09.857 --> 09:10.954
You all right?

09:10.957 --> 09:12.607
When we busted into that Morlock tunnel,

09:12.610 --> 09:14.424
I was expecting to see a terrorist camp.

09:14.427 --> 09:16.361
That's what Ryan told me was there.

09:16.363 --> 09:18.463
I think there were kids down there, man.

09:20.233 --> 09:21.299
Jace, listen, uh...

09:22.369 --> 09:24.082
...this may sound harsh, but

09:24.085 --> 09:26.621
if there were kids down
there, they're gonna grow up

09:26.624 --> 09:28.373
to be the same monsters
that killed our friends.

09:28.375 --> 09:29.374
How could...

09:29.376 --> 09:30.708
How can you say that?

09:30.710 --> 09:33.878
You don't know that.
You don't know that.

09:37.083 --> 09:39.217
All right, you know, um...

09:39.219 --> 09:41.300
you have done more
than enough for the day.

09:41.303 --> 09:43.721
Why don't you head back to
your hotel and clear your head?

09:43.723 --> 09:45.323
All right?

09:45.325 --> 09:46.658
We got this.

09:50.664 --> 09:52.664
Let's head out.

09:56.636 --> 09:58.636
- [KNOCKING]
- Hey.

09:58.638 --> 10:01.139
Heard you were coming
on the scout tonight.

10:01.141 --> 10:02.941
Yeah.

10:02.943 --> 10:05.922
I don't know. I'm just curious. Why?

10:05.925 --> 10:07.779
You think I need
babysitting or something?

10:07.781 --> 10:09.614
No, not at all.

10:09.616 --> 10:12.750
All right, 'cause I can handle myself.

10:12.752 --> 10:14.319
Yeah, I know. [LAUGHS SOFTLY]

10:14.321 --> 10:18.356
No. I... I just want
to see what we're doing.

10:18.358 --> 10:21.326
Like you said, it's
been a long time coming.

10:21.328 --> 10:23.795
All right, just making sure.

10:25.531 --> 10:29.644
Andy? Um... you know when we do this,

10:29.647 --> 10:31.836
it's not gonna be like
a video game, right?

10:31.838 --> 10:35.106
When everything goes down, we're
gonna be dropping real buildings

10:35.108 --> 10:37.475
with... real people inside.

10:37.477 --> 10:41.212
Yeah, I mean, we have to
make sacrifices sometimes.

10:42.949 --> 10:44.515
You taught me that.

10:45.952 --> 10:47.605
- I did?
- Yeah.

10:47.608 --> 10:50.123
When you ripped that plane out
of the sky and saved us all.

10:50.126 --> 10:52.490
That's the whole reason
I joined the Inner Circle.

10:57.731 --> 11:01.132
Andy, look, uh...

11:01.134 --> 11:03.801
you know that wasn't easy, right?

11:05.138 --> 11:07.138
You do something like that...

11:08.808 --> 11:10.908
...those scars stay with you.

11:12.991 --> 11:15.525
I guess I'll have a few scars, then.

11:21.254 --> 11:22.887
[SIGHS]

11:22.889 --> 11:25.423
ECLIPSE: Yeah, he was right here.

11:25.425 --> 11:27.492
[SIREN WAILING IN DISTANCE]

11:27.494 --> 11:29.023
What the hell is he doing?

11:29.026 --> 11:30.561
I got to go talk to him.

11:30.563 --> 11:32.230
I hope you fare better than that wall.

11:32.232 --> 11:33.964
Keep an eye on the street, all right?

11:33.967 --> 11:37.112
- It's a miracle the cops haven't found him yet.
- Yeah.

11:39.239 --> 11:41.773
[GRUNTING LOUDLY]

11:41.775 --> 11:43.241
John...

11:43.243 --> 11:46.511
uh... what are you doing?

11:46.513 --> 11:48.546
I can't leave her.

11:48.548 --> 11:50.548
Who? Clarice? What happened? Where is...

11:50.550 --> 11:52.550
She got shot.

11:52.552 --> 11:56.054
- Oh, my God. She, uh...
- I don't know.

11:56.056 --> 11:59.924
She fell. She fell through
a portal and she vanished.

12:02.028 --> 12:04.028
I saw it happen.

12:04.030 --> 12:07.432
I saw... I saw her fall.

12:09.269 --> 12:10.868
[GRUNTING]

12:10.870 --> 12:13.938
Look, I'm sorry, um, John,

12:13.940 --> 12:16.112
but you just said she's,
uh, she's not here.

12:16.115 --> 12:17.575
You don't understand.

12:17.577 --> 12:20.645
I can still feel her.

12:24.784 --> 12:27.952
[HELICOPTER APPROACHING]

12:27.954 --> 12:30.588
[HELICOPTER PASSING OVERHEAD]

12:30.590 --> 12:34.125
[SIRENS WAILING IN DISTANCE]

12:34.127 --> 12:36.292
[PURIFIER SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY NEARBY]

12:36.295 --> 12:38.629
Yeah, I heard something.
What do you think?

12:38.631 --> 12:40.631
Let's see.

12:41.901 --> 12:45.236
PURIFIER: Might have gotten
further than we thought.

12:45.238 --> 12:47.338
All clear here.

12:47.340 --> 12:49.474
Let's check further down.

12:49.476 --> 12:51.776
Make sure you look up, too.

12:51.778 --> 12:53.778
[VOICE FADES]

12:54.981 --> 12:57.248
Sir?

12:57.250 --> 13:00.852
I'm gonna need you to
turn around, real slow.

13:06.626 --> 13:09.494
You seem awful worried
about my pals over there.

13:09.496 --> 13:11.329
You want to tell me why?

13:11.331 --> 13:14.458
I saw men with...
assault rifles outside,

13:14.461 --> 13:15.967
and I was concerned.

13:15.969 --> 13:17.538
Is that right?

13:17.541 --> 13:19.770
So you're out here walking around,

13:19.773 --> 13:21.506
checking out dumpsters?

13:21.508 --> 13:23.174
It's not a crime, is it?

13:23.176 --> 13:24.809
I work in the area, all right?

13:24.811 --> 13:26.082
There were sirens.

13:26.085 --> 13:27.712
Heard there was a
possible mutant incident,

13:27.714 --> 13:29.947
and I came outside to
make sure it was safe.

13:34.320 --> 13:35.924
All right. [CHUCKLES]

13:35.927 --> 13:37.051
- [EXHALES]
- All right, sir,

13:37.054 --> 13:38.488
yeah, it just, uh...

13:38.491 --> 13:40.024
just looked a little odd.

13:40.026 --> 13:41.626
Thank you.

13:41.628 --> 13:43.628
[LOW CRACKLING]

13:48.401 --> 13:49.967
[STRAINING]

13:53.907 --> 13:55.406
Don't move!

13:55.408 --> 13:56.908
Don't you make a sound.

13:56.910 --> 13:59.310
You looking for your mutie friends? Huh?

13:59.312 --> 14:02.222
We're not gonna stop
till we wipe you all out!

14:02.225 --> 14:04.148
Shut up! Shut up!

14:06.653 --> 14:08.219
[WILSON GRUNTING]

14:08.221 --> 14:09.887
[CRACKLING]

14:12.225 --> 14:14.859
[GASPING BREATHS]

14:16.930 --> 14:19.764
[BREATH TREMBLING]

14:19.766 --> 14:22.366
This is crazy. Look, you
think she's in that wall?

14:22.368 --> 14:24.402
[GRUNTS] I'm not leaving her!

14:24.404 --> 14:26.831
REED: Guys! We need to go! Now!

14:26.834 --> 14:28.506
There's Purifiers out on the street!

14:28.508 --> 14:31.008
- [PANTING]
- You heard him.

14:31.010 --> 14:32.577
[SHOUTS]

14:34.681 --> 14:35.913
John!

14:35.915 --> 14:37.615
- Hey...
- Hey!

14:37.617 --> 14:39.556
- [GROANS]
- [GASPS]

14:39.559 --> 14:42.019
The Purifiers are here,
the cops aren't far behind.

14:42.021 --> 14:43.521
Listen to me.

14:43.523 --> 14:45.389
What would Clarice want you to do?

14:46.392 --> 14:48.526
Now, you know the answer.

14:48.528 --> 14:50.294
Now, come on.

14:50.296 --> 14:51.929
Go, go, go.

15:05.854 --> 15:08.855
♪ ♪

15:08.857 --> 15:10.123
Come on.

15:13.471 --> 15:15.423
Looks like it's empty.

15:15.426 --> 15:17.096
Maybe we can find a phone inside.

15:17.098 --> 15:18.798
- [GUNSHOTS IN DISTANCE]
- The police are

15:18.800 --> 15:21.100
hunting down the Morlocks.
We need to go back for them.

15:21.102 --> 15:22.802
We are past that point.

15:22.804 --> 15:25.805
We just need to be thankful
that we got out of there.

15:28.376 --> 15:30.309
Did you know?

15:31.813 --> 15:33.479
Know what?

15:33.481 --> 15:36.115
That if we split up,
they'd slow the cops down,

15:36.117 --> 15:37.416
help us escape.

15:42.090 --> 15:44.750
I knew that if we stayed on the road,

15:44.753 --> 15:46.656
we were all gonna get caught.

15:46.659 --> 15:50.229
Cars with that many bullet
holes are pretty easy to find.

15:50.231 --> 15:52.131
There was no way we
were all gonna escape.

15:52.133 --> 15:54.100
They're dying out there.

15:54.102 --> 15:56.836
There's a good chance they're
gonna track us down, too.

15:58.339 --> 15:59.972
[PANTING]: Look...

15:59.974 --> 16:01.841
I hate all of this.

16:01.843 --> 16:03.596
It breaks my heart.

16:03.599 --> 16:05.745
But people are depending on us.

16:05.747 --> 16:07.980
We have to get through this.

16:09.317 --> 16:11.617
Now, please, just get inside.

16:13.421 --> 16:16.823
♪ ♪

16:19.527 --> 16:20.993
[SIGHS]

16:22.263 --> 16:24.030
[DOOR OPENS]

16:24.032 --> 16:26.681
Checked the whole building...
No sign of Lauren or Caitlin.

16:26.684 --> 16:28.267
They're not answering their phones.

16:28.269 --> 16:31.037
Something is wrong. We've got
to get out there and find them.

16:31.039 --> 16:33.339
[DISTORTED, ECHOING]: Good girl!

16:34.843 --> 16:37.443
[DISTORTED, ECHOING BARKING]

16:37.445 --> 16:38.895
REED: John?

16:38.980 --> 16:40.046
John?

16:40.048 --> 16:41.814
We have some idea

16:41.816 --> 16:43.933
of the route that
Lauren and Caitlin took.

16:43.936 --> 16:46.685
- If you could track them...
- I can't.

16:46.688 --> 16:49.021
I can't imagine what
you're going through, but...

16:49.023 --> 16:50.656
if there is any way...

16:50.658 --> 16:52.391
I-I can't track.

16:52.393 --> 16:54.660
I want to help you find
your family, all right?

16:54.662 --> 16:57.129
But every time I try,
I just see Clarice.

16:59.402 --> 17:01.734
We have got to find them.
We've got to do something.

17:01.736 --> 17:03.236
Hey, take it... take it easy.

17:03.238 --> 17:05.905
Whoa. Whoa.

17:17.085 --> 17:19.518
So, where exactly are we going?

17:19.520 --> 17:21.768
The sewage tunnel system underneath D.C.

17:21.771 --> 17:23.990
There's an entrance at
the train yard near here.

17:23.992 --> 17:26.259
Train yard. Cool.

17:26.261 --> 17:28.394
I used to have a thing for trains.

17:28.396 --> 17:31.558
You know if you lined up every
railroad track in America,

17:31.561 --> 17:33.532
it would wrap around
the world five times?

17:33.534 --> 17:35.167
What are you, Wiki-Andy?

17:36.604 --> 17:39.005
There was this kid in my physics class,

17:39.007 --> 17:40.673
freshman year.

17:40.675 --> 17:43.145
He didn't have a lot of
friends. He was kind of weird.

17:43.148 --> 17:45.511
And he was super into trains.

17:45.513 --> 17:46.836
I used to sit with him at lunch,

17:46.839 --> 17:48.282
and he'd teach me all about them.

17:50.184 --> 17:51.751
We're here.

18:00.728 --> 18:02.028
Ugh.

18:02.030 --> 18:03.729
Told you we should've worn flats.

18:03.731 --> 18:05.097
Ugh. As if.

18:05.099 --> 18:07.934
This tunnel system will
give us access to the city.

18:07.936 --> 18:10.109
So these tunnels were always here.

18:10.112 --> 18:12.474
Why haven't we been down here before?

18:12.477 --> 18:13.806
Everything in its time.

18:13.808 --> 18:15.574
[BULK STRAINING]

18:15.576 --> 18:17.977
[PANTING]

18:17.979 --> 18:19.912
Have fun down there.

18:25.153 --> 18:27.895
POLARIS: So, what
exactly are we doing here

18:27.898 --> 18:29.722
besides catching typhoid?

18:29.724 --> 18:31.924
One of the tunnels shares a wall

18:31.926 --> 18:34.093
with the D.C. Sentinel
Services headquarters.

18:34.095 --> 18:36.662
Andrew's gonna get us through
the wall with a strike team.

18:36.664 --> 18:39.209
Once the Sentinel
Services is neutralized,

18:39.212 --> 18:41.334
we will be unstoppable.

18:41.336 --> 18:44.136
Neutralized? You mean
I'm going in there, too?

18:44.138 --> 18:46.387
To, like... kill them?

18:46.390 --> 18:47.974
Is that a problem?

18:50.411 --> 18:52.578
- No, of course not.
- Excellent.

18:54.582 --> 18:57.116
[SIRENS WAILING IN DISTANCE]

18:57.118 --> 19:00.853
All this equipment and
not a single landline.

19:00.855 --> 19:02.588
Even if we found
something, I highly doubt

19:02.590 --> 19:04.757
this place has paid their
phone bill in a while.

19:04.759 --> 19:06.258
If we can find something,

19:06.260 --> 19:08.792
we might be able to
splice into an open wire.

19:08.795 --> 19:09.996
Anything.

19:09.998 --> 19:13.966
[HELICOPTER BLADES
WHIRRING, DOGS BARKING]

19:13.968 --> 19:16.669
[SIRENS APPROACHING]

19:16.671 --> 19:18.670
The cops figured out we're in here.

19:18.673 --> 19:20.559
COP: That dog's getting
a pretty good hit!

19:20.569 --> 19:23.009
[GASPS] It's just a matter of time.

19:23.011 --> 19:25.196
- Maybe we can run.
- No, we're not gonna outrun

19:25.199 --> 19:27.213
dogs and a helicopter.

19:27.215 --> 19:29.641
- COP: Let's move in!
- Your powers,

19:29.644 --> 19:31.351
is there anything...?

19:33.321 --> 19:34.987
I can't feel them. I'm sorry.

19:34.989 --> 19:37.556
That's okay. We'll
figure something else out.

19:39.519 --> 19:42.528
Let's see if we can find
anything else to use as weapons.

19:42.530 --> 19:45.364
What are we gonna do,
throw pipes at them?

19:45.366 --> 19:49.001
If we surrender,
everything we fought for,

19:49.003 --> 19:51.370
everything we've lost
will be for nothing.

19:52.707 --> 19:54.040
[PANTING]

19:54.042 --> 19:56.742
We've come too far to give up now.

19:59.147 --> 20:00.980
[INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER]

20:00.982 --> 20:03.015
ECLIPSE: Anything on the scanner?

20:04.052 --> 20:06.252
THUNDERBIRD: Not yet.

20:07.822 --> 20:09.422
Can I get a hit of that?

20:10.892 --> 20:12.258
Thanks.

20:13.261 --> 20:15.243
So, your powers...

20:15.246 --> 20:16.929
They're back.

20:18.266 --> 20:20.232
Yeah. I stopped taking the medicine.

20:20.234 --> 20:22.034
Got to learn to control this thing.

20:22.036 --> 20:24.003
It's always come and gone with stress.

20:28.709 --> 20:31.544
When you first got your abilities...

20:31.546 --> 20:33.746
did you know what they were for?

20:33.748 --> 20:36.115
I mean, why you had them?

20:36.117 --> 20:40.324
I wasn't really having a lot
of philosophical discussions,

20:40.327 --> 20:43.689
'cause I was busy
finding a place to sleep.

20:43.691 --> 20:46.058
But you must have thought about it.

20:46.060 --> 20:50.463
My father told me that the
Devil gave me my powers.

20:50.465 --> 20:53.365
[SCOFFS SOFTLY]

20:53.367 --> 20:56.268
As much as I hated the man,
on some level I think I agreed.

20:56.270 --> 20:59.105
And I was in a dark place.

21:03.611 --> 21:05.926
Reed, what's going on?
Did something happen?

21:05.929 --> 21:07.913
- THUNDERBIRD: Hey, listen up.
- DISPATCHER: ...two suspects

21:07.915 --> 21:09.982
hiding out in a water
treatment facility.

21:09.984 --> 21:12.179
I repeat: All units be advised,

21:12.182 --> 21:14.316
10-80M in progress.

21:14.319 --> 21:17.089
Canine unit picked up
two suspects hiding out...

21:17.091 --> 21:18.757
That's close to where
we rescued the Morlocks.

21:18.759 --> 21:20.659
- Do you think...
- I think we should assume the worst.

21:20.661 --> 21:22.628
- ECLIPSE: You good?
- Yeah.

21:22.630 --> 21:24.216
Reed and I will go. Keep
an eye on the scanner.

21:24.218 --> 21:25.196
Let me know if anything changes.

21:25.198 --> 21:26.564
- I should come.
- John, you know

21:26.567 --> 21:29.234
you're in no position
to do anything right now.

21:29.237 --> 21:30.836
We got this, brother.

21:37.645 --> 21:39.599
The others will be back
once Reeva gives them

21:39.602 --> 21:41.975
their assignments. You
two should get some rest

21:41.978 --> 21:44.879
before tomorrow's... festivities.

21:44.881 --> 21:47.782
Yeah, uh, festivities. Yeah.

21:48.818 --> 21:50.451
Good night.

21:50.454 --> 21:51.953
Hey, Esme.

21:53.823 --> 21:55.122
What about you?

21:55.124 --> 21:57.491
- What about me?
- I'm taking out

21:57.493 --> 21:59.160
the communications grid.

21:59.162 --> 22:01.250
Andy's hitting Sentinel Services.

22:01.253 --> 22:02.663
What are you doing?

22:02.665 --> 22:05.366
- Uh, we're really not supposed to get into that.
- Come on.

22:05.368 --> 22:07.234
Secret's out tomorrow, anyway.

22:10.473 --> 22:13.140
[CHUCKLES SOFTLY]

22:13.142 --> 22:15.142
Let me put it this way.

22:15.144 --> 22:17.878
Once the situation gets bad enough,

22:17.880 --> 22:20.347
it's our job to help people understand

22:20.349 --> 22:23.017
that a mutant homeland is the answer.

22:23.019 --> 22:25.586
You mean force people to understand.

22:27.423 --> 22:30.357
[SIGHS] You really okay with that?

22:30.359 --> 22:32.593
- We're willing to do what's necessary.
- We?

22:32.595 --> 22:35.322
No, I'm not talking about your
sisters. I'm talking about you.

22:35.325 --> 22:37.898
Look, I'm just asking you, seriously,

22:37.900 --> 22:39.366
do you really think

22:39.368 --> 22:41.869
that we can mind-control
our way to a mutant homeland?

22:43.706 --> 22:46.340
Don't we want people to believe?

22:47.376 --> 22:49.376
Maybe someday.

22:50.880 --> 22:52.746
We won you over.

22:54.717 --> 22:56.550
There might be hope for the world.

22:58.588 --> 23:01.122
Good night, Lorna.

23:04.560 --> 23:06.794
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

23:06.796 --> 23:08.863
[DOGS BARKING]

23:12.602 --> 23:14.768
- They're coming in.
- No, they're not.

23:15.605 --> 23:17.371
Get down.

23:17.373 --> 23:19.106
Take cover! Pull back!

23:19.909 --> 23:21.709
Open fire!

23:26.616 --> 23:28.315
Hold your fire!

23:28.317 --> 23:29.950
- Hold your fire!
- CAITLIN: They're gonna call

23:29.952 --> 23:31.318
for reinforcements.

23:31.320 --> 23:33.365
And I've only got three bullets left.

23:33.368 --> 23:35.156
Ah, come on.

23:36.759 --> 23:39.059
We need a plan.

23:39.061 --> 23:41.629
- [INDISTINCT SHOUTING]
- [GASPS] We're trapped.

23:41.631 --> 23:43.631
There's no way.

23:45.635 --> 23:48.569
Yes, there is.

23:48.571 --> 23:50.571
When they come back,

23:50.573 --> 23:52.273
if I can create a big enough distraction

23:52.275 --> 23:53.507
to draw them to the front,

23:53.509 --> 23:54.942
then you can get out the loading door

23:54.944 --> 23:56.944
- and run off before they can catch you.
- No.

23:56.946 --> 23:59.468
- No, I'm not leaving you.
- We don't have a choice.

23:59.471 --> 24:02.183
I-I can't hold them
off. If you can run...

24:02.185 --> 24:03.584
- No, I'm not running, Mom.
- Hey.

24:03.586 --> 24:05.054
You have powers.

24:05.057 --> 24:07.006
Maybe you can't control them right now,

24:07.009 --> 24:08.422
but they will come back.

24:08.424 --> 24:10.424
- [CRYING]: No, please don't leave me. Mom.
- Hey, Lauren.

24:10.426 --> 24:12.126
- Just listen to me. Please.
- No, please, please.

24:12.128 --> 24:13.334
Please.

24:13.337 --> 24:15.262
You are gonna fight for all the mutants.

24:15.264 --> 24:16.864
For Andy.

24:16.866 --> 24:18.132
You can change the destiny

24:18.134 --> 24:19.778
of the whole von Strucker family.

24:19.781 --> 24:21.080
You're part of that family.

24:21.938 --> 24:23.637
I'm not leaving you!

24:25.274 --> 24:28.209
Yeah. [GASPS]

24:28.211 --> 24:30.711
Your powers. They're back.

24:30.713 --> 24:32.680
I guess so.

24:32.682 --> 24:34.782
We can do this.

24:34.784 --> 24:36.784
- Yeah.
- Together.

24:38.120 --> 24:40.474
I've done the research, okay?

24:40.477 --> 24:44.046
Stores near sewer entry points
report twice as many robberies.

24:44.049 --> 24:46.227
And they're taking food, supplies.

24:46.229 --> 24:49.610
The point is, people say there's
no such thing as Morlocks,

24:49.613 --> 24:51.580
but that's because they're not looking.

24:51.583 --> 24:54.579
They refuse to see. The truth is there.

24:54.582 --> 24:56.563
Just take a look at
this security footage

24:56.566 --> 24:59.672
from right here in D.C.
under our very noses.

25:22.697 --> 25:25.665
[DOGS BARKING]

25:25.668 --> 25:28.502
Well, it looks like we found them.

25:28.504 --> 25:30.704
How the hell do we get in there, though?

25:30.706 --> 25:32.539
[HELICOPTER BLADES WHIRRING]

25:37.546 --> 25:40.643
Can you do that thing where you
hide us by absorbing the light?

25:40.646 --> 25:43.127
Well, I can probably
get us past the cops.

25:43.130 --> 25:44.685
But they're gonna notice a black shadow

25:44.687 --> 25:45.807
climbing through the window.

25:48.052 --> 25:50.190
- I might be able to get us in there.
- How, Reed?

25:50.192 --> 25:51.959
They've got all the entrances covered.

25:51.961 --> 25:53.961
I'll make a new one.

25:53.963 --> 25:56.697
Get me to the building, and
I'll break through the wall.

25:58.801 --> 26:01.101
And what if you can't?

26:01.103 --> 26:02.786
We have no choice.

26:02.789 --> 26:04.371
COP: Get ready! Get ready!

26:04.373 --> 26:05.639
All right.

26:05.641 --> 26:07.033
I'll turn out the lights.

26:07.036 --> 26:08.442
The rest is up to you.

26:11.914 --> 26:13.881
[EXHALES]

26:40.976 --> 26:42.976
[EXHALES]

26:45.981 --> 26:47.981
Andy?

26:48.984 --> 26:50.617
Oh, hey.

26:50.619 --> 26:53.320
I'm just, uh, psyching
myself up for tomorrow.

26:56.325 --> 26:57.791
What's wrong?

27:00.496 --> 27:02.496
- [SIGHS]
- ANDY: That's crazy.

27:02.498 --> 27:04.565
Reeva would never work
with the Purifiers.

27:04.568 --> 27:06.100
I saw her myself.

27:06.102 --> 27:09.312
- She was meeting with Benedict Ryan.
- Benedict Ry...

27:09.315 --> 27:11.104
Sh-She hates him. She hates them all.

27:11.107 --> 27:12.139
- Why would she...
- Because they both want

27:12.141 --> 27:13.474
the same thing, Andy.

27:13.476 --> 27:16.009
Mutants and humans living apart.

27:16.011 --> 27:17.811
She needs people angry.

27:17.813 --> 27:19.179
She needs the Purifiers.

27:19.181 --> 27:21.215
They want us dead. Why
would they help her?

27:21.217 --> 27:23.486
She's using them to
take out her competition

27:23.489 --> 27:25.352
so her mutant uprising
is all that's left.

27:25.354 --> 27:26.887
That's insane.

27:26.889 --> 27:28.322
I don't believe that.

27:28.324 --> 27:30.624
Andy.

27:30.626 --> 27:33.827
Remember earlier when
she wouldn't tell us why

27:33.829 --> 27:36.663
we've never been in
those tunnels before?

27:36.665 --> 27:40.300
There were mutants living there, Andy.

27:40.302 --> 27:43.170
Families.

27:43.172 --> 27:45.843
The Purifiers wiped them out for her.

27:45.846 --> 27:48.395
So you're telling me that
everything Reeva said was a lie.

27:48.398 --> 27:50.310
Everything we did.

27:51.347 --> 27:54.548
Rebecca died for a lie?

27:56.018 --> 27:57.885
Look, I didn't want
to believe it, either.

27:57.887 --> 27:59.887
But it's true.

27:59.889 --> 28:01.722
I know how you feel, okay?

28:01.725 --> 28:04.592
I want a mutant homeland,
too, but not like this.

28:07.563 --> 28:10.864
Andy, we... we can stop her.

28:12.835 --> 28:15.369
If you come with me.

28:21.762 --> 28:24.070
Andy, we have to get out of here now.

28:24.072 --> 28:25.738
No, I-I'm sorry.

28:25.740 --> 28:27.139
- I can't leave.
- Wait.

28:27.141 --> 28:28.274
What?

28:28.276 --> 28:29.375
What do you mean?

28:29.377 --> 28:30.676
Don't you want to go
back to your family?

28:30.678 --> 28:31.878
Yeah, but how can I?

28:31.880 --> 28:33.257
After everything that happened.

28:35.350 --> 28:37.350
Andy.

28:43.358 --> 28:45.424
Andy.

28:49.731 --> 28:53.253
You can't stay here, can you?

28:53.256 --> 28:55.568
- Knowing what you know?
- I don't know.

28:55.570 --> 28:57.403
After all the things I've done...

28:59.207 --> 29:00.940
Maybe I belong here.

29:00.942 --> 29:03.743
No. Andy, that story you told me
about the boy who loved trains,

29:03.746 --> 29:05.768
the one you sat with at
school when no one else would.

29:05.770 --> 29:07.856
Andy Strucke that is who you are.

29:07.859 --> 29:09.639
Yeah, maybe a long time ago, Lorna.

29:09.642 --> 29:11.852
But I'm not that person anymore.

29:13.318 --> 29:16.187
[INDISTINCT CHATTER]

29:16.190 --> 29:17.723
[SCREECHING]

29:21.840 --> 29:23.607
All right, you're up.

29:23.610 --> 29:27.966
[SIREN WAILING]

29:27.969 --> 29:29.969
[EXHALES]

29:29.971 --> 29:33.372
[GRUNTING]

29:36.811 --> 29:39.033
COP [OVER LOUDSPEAKER]:
This is your last warning.

29:39.036 --> 29:41.715
Come out with your hands up.

29:52.160 --> 29:55.394
[INDISTINCT SHOUTING]

29:55.396 --> 29:57.763
- [EXHALES]
- Not bad.

29:57.765 --> 29:59.231
I try.

30:01.402 --> 30:03.269
Listen to me, Reed.

30:03.271 --> 30:05.304
We don't have a plan B.

30:05.306 --> 30:06.663
[GRUNTS]

30:06.666 --> 30:08.386
And your wife and your daughter,

30:08.389 --> 30:10.076
they're in there, and
they need your help.

30:10.078 --> 30:11.884
I know what you're trying
to do, and it is not helping.

30:11.886 --> 30:14.055
- You're letting them down.
- I wish I could turn my powers

30:14.057 --> 30:15.737
on and off like everyone
else, but I can't.

30:16.818 --> 30:18.451
Reed?

30:23.925 --> 30:25.624
[EXHALES]

30:25.626 --> 30:27.326
Better late than never.

30:27.328 --> 30:28.794
Yeah, I'll say.

30:29.797 --> 30:31.797
[EXHALES]

30:36.537 --> 30:38.871
The building's surrounded.

30:38.873 --> 30:40.473
We have to hold them off.

30:40.475 --> 30:43.209
[RUMBLING]

30:43.211 --> 30:45.444
Where's that coming from?

30:46.447 --> 30:48.047
The wall.

30:54.489 --> 30:56.489
[REED GRUNTING]

30:57.725 --> 30:59.191
[GASPS] Reed.

30:59.849 --> 31:01.160
LAUREN: Dad, you did it.

31:01.162 --> 31:02.655
You two okay?

31:02.658 --> 31:04.999
- We are now.
- ECLIPSE: Guys, it's really good to see you,

31:05.002 --> 31:06.652
but the cops are gonna
know something's up soon.

31:06.654 --> 31:07.733
Just stay close

31:07.735 --> 31:09.255
- and stay quiet, all right?
- Come on.

31:14.208 --> 31:16.175
That's pretty cool.

31:26.187 --> 31:27.501
Yeah, we got lucky.

31:27.504 --> 31:29.488
Helicopter still thinks
you're in that building.

31:29.490 --> 31:31.557
I guess that's one
thing that went right.

31:31.559 --> 31:33.092
Hmm.

31:33.094 --> 31:34.527
I can't believe Clarice is gone.

31:36.097 --> 31:37.563
What happened?

31:37.565 --> 31:40.253
She stayed back in the tunnels

31:40.256 --> 31:42.568
to rescue the last of the Morlocks.

31:45.907 --> 31:47.106
How's John?

31:47.108 --> 31:49.575
- He must be...
- He's a wreck.

31:50.745 --> 31:52.244
- [SIGHS]
- [PHONE VIBRATES]

31:52.246 --> 31:54.099
- Yeah.
- Hello?

31:54.102 --> 31:55.581
POLARIS: Reed, it's Lorna.

31:55.583 --> 31:56.715
I'm with Andy.

31:56.717 --> 31:58.784
He needs to talk to you.

32:00.888 --> 32:02.354
Yeah, of course.

32:02.356 --> 32:03.589
Put him on.

32:07.195 --> 32:09.195
Andy, come on.

32:09.197 --> 32:11.363
REED: Andy, are you there?

32:12.433 --> 32:13.632
He's on the phone?

32:13.634 --> 32:14.767
I think so.

32:14.769 --> 32:16.702
Are you there, son?

32:16.704 --> 32:18.704
Dad?

32:18.706 --> 32:20.039
Andy, I know the things

32:20.041 --> 32:21.574
that Lorna is saying to you

32:21.576 --> 32:23.876
are hard to hear, but...

32:23.878 --> 32:26.278
they are true. You need to come home.

32:26.280 --> 32:27.313
[EXHALES]

32:28.382 --> 32:30.549
REED: Andy.

32:36.457 --> 32:39.458
I'm sorry.

32:39.460 --> 32:42.568
- I don't think I can do that.
- REED: What? Course you can.

32:42.571 --> 32:44.163
We love you so much.

32:44.165 --> 32:46.042
We're your family. You belong with us.

32:46.045 --> 32:47.233
ANDY: Do I?

32:47.235 --> 32:49.568
When we saved John,

32:49.570 --> 32:53.139
when I attacked that Purifier
for trying to shoot Lauren...

32:54.675 --> 32:56.675
...I saw you, Dad.

32:57.678 --> 32:59.945
- You were afraid of me.
- REED: No.

32:59.947 --> 33:01.536
Andy, th-that's...

33:01.539 --> 33:03.341
- that's not...
- ANDY: You know it's true, Dad.

33:03.343 --> 33:04.576
And you were right.

33:05.419 --> 33:06.852
I wanted to kill that man.

33:06.854 --> 33:09.188
[SNIFFLES]

33:09.190 --> 33:12.124
I belong here.

33:12.126 --> 33:14.326
I am a monster.

33:16.164 --> 33:18.264
Hey, what is he saying?

33:18.266 --> 33:20.766
ANDY: You don't have to
say anything else. I just...

33:20.768 --> 33:22.701
I just wanted you to
understand why I can't come.

33:22.703 --> 33:24.770
Wait, Andy, please. Listen to me.

33:27.041 --> 33:30.142
I do understand.

33:30.144 --> 33:31.777
More than you know.

33:33.381 --> 33:35.381
Today, I...

33:36.450 --> 33:38.450
[SIGHS]

33:38.452 --> 33:39.985
I killed a man.

33:43.391 --> 33:44.557
[EXHALES]

33:46.060 --> 33:48.727
He was threatening us, and...

33:48.729 --> 33:50.863
[EXHALES]

33:50.865 --> 33:52.698
He, um...

33:52.700 --> 33:54.166
he was...

33:54.168 --> 33:56.835
I-I got so angry, and...

33:56.837 --> 33:58.671
and I lost control.

33:58.673 --> 34:00.673
- And...
- Hey...

34:00.675 --> 34:02.007
...and I killed him.

34:02.009 --> 34:04.476
Not because...

34:04.478 --> 34:07.479
I had to but...

34:07.481 --> 34:10.081
because I wanted to.

34:14.088 --> 34:16.255
So,

34:16.257 --> 34:18.524
if you're a monster, son, then so am I.

34:19.860 --> 34:22.527
I-I have to go.

34:22.530 --> 34:24.897
[SIGHS]

34:26.333 --> 34:28.833
What'd he say?

34:28.835 --> 34:30.369
Is he coming home?

34:32.907 --> 34:34.340
I don't know.

34:35.576 --> 34:37.409
[EXHALES]

34:48.101 --> 34:50.936
I thought we had more
canned goods than this.

34:50.938 --> 34:53.572
I guess we haven't been
to the store in a while.

34:53.574 --> 34:55.574
I don't think the
Morlocks are gonna be picky

34:55.576 --> 34:57.976
about creamed versus canned corn.

34:57.978 --> 35:00.012
- [CHUCKLES SOFTLY]
- At least they're safe.

35:04.803 --> 35:06.202
Reed,

35:06.205 --> 35:08.453
if you hadn't stopped that man,

35:08.455 --> 35:10.022
he would have shot you.

35:10.024 --> 35:11.690
You didn't have a choice.

35:13.127 --> 35:15.153
I'd already destroyed his gun, Cait.

35:15.156 --> 35:17.029
And if you walked away,
he would have called

35:17.031 --> 35:18.864
his friends or-or the police.

35:18.866 --> 35:20.866
None of you would've
made it out of there.

35:22.906 --> 35:24.036
Hey.

35:25.339 --> 35:27.272
You are a good man.

35:28.309 --> 35:30.776
I know that.

35:33.773 --> 35:36.273
I don't think he's coming home.

35:36.276 --> 35:38.350
We don't know what's gonna happen.

35:38.352 --> 35:40.852
The important thing is
you told him the truth.

35:40.854 --> 35:44.690
Is it me? And, I mean,
my family history, my...

35:44.692 --> 35:46.525
What I did to that man today,

35:46.527 --> 35:49.628
what if it's all just...

35:49.630 --> 35:51.029
[SHUDDERS]

35:51.031 --> 35:53.031
What if it's all just darkness?

35:58.376 --> 36:02.394
Maybe you had to join
Andy in that darkness...

36:03.844 --> 36:05.744
...in order to help him.

36:09.183 --> 36:11.350
All you can do is show him the path.

36:12.820 --> 36:14.653
You can't make him take it.

36:23.664 --> 36:24.997
[KNOCKING]

36:24.999 --> 36:26.198
[DOOR OPENS]

36:27.636 --> 36:29.034
Hey, man.

36:29.036 --> 36:30.902
Everybody make it?

36:30.904 --> 36:32.704
Yeah. Yeah.

36:37.411 --> 36:39.444
I'm sorry I couldn't be there.

36:39.446 --> 36:41.546
[SIGHS] How are you?

36:42.549 --> 36:44.349
I'm not good. Um...

36:46.854 --> 36:48.754
It-it hurts. I just...

36:48.756 --> 36:50.055
I-I miss her.

36:50.057 --> 36:51.890
[CRYING]

36:51.892 --> 36:54.760
Everyone that I love dies.

36:54.762 --> 36:56.962
Hey. Look, you can't...
You can't blame yourself.

36:56.964 --> 36:59.531
She didn't die in vain.

36:59.533 --> 37:02.901
Every Morlock who's standing
is alive because of her.

37:02.903 --> 37:06.772
Doesn't stop me from hating
myself for not saving her.

37:08.642 --> 37:09.975
I'm useless.

37:09.977 --> 37:12.244
You're not useless, John.

37:13.814 --> 37:15.914
So what if you can't track?

37:15.916 --> 37:17.983
So what?

37:17.985 --> 37:20.884
The storm that's coming our
way isn't gonna be hard to find.

37:20.887 --> 37:23.588
And the real question here, brother,

37:23.590 --> 37:25.757
